authnSelectionTrees.name: AuthN with CSP Pickers Based on IAL Values and Session Check
authnSelectionTrees.description: This policy is the policy the IRS will use to authenticate users to IAL1 or IAL2 PA protected apps.   The policy will check the IAL level, then check to see if the user has authenticated with that level (or higher) before.   If so, it uses the existing session data.   If not, the user is given a CSP menu.

authnSelectionTrees.name: AuthN with CSP Pickers Based on IAL Values and Session Check with Fragments
authnSelectionTrees.description: This policy is the policy the IRS will use to authenticate users to IAL1 or IAL2 PA protected apps.   The policy will check the IAL level, then check to see if the user has authenticated with that level (or higher) before.   If so, it uses the existing session data.   If not, the user is given a CSP menu.   This version uses fragments to encapsulate the connections to the IdP connections

authnSelectionTrees.name: AuthN with CSP Pickers Based on Forced IAL Values and Session Check-with Fragments
authnSelectionTrees.description: This policy is the policy the IRS will use to authenticate users to IAL1 or IAL2 PA protected apps.   The policy will check the forceIAL selector and, if true, then use the forcedIALToUse selector to determin the IAL level, then check to see if the user has authenticated with that level (or higher) before.   If so, it uses the existing session data.   If not, the user is given a CSP menu.
